abstract: ATTRACTIONS    Museums and Sites    MUSEUM OF THE CITY OF NEW YORK, Fifth Avenue at 103rd Street. The museum collects, preserves and presents material related to the city's history. Tomorrow at 2 p.m., a lecture by Patrick Downey, author of ''Gangster City.'' Through Sept. 26, ''New York's Moynihan,'' an exhibition of photographs, letters, videos and other items. ''Magnum's New Yorkers,'' with 130 photographs covering 50 years in the city's history; and ''Global New York: The Lower East Side,'' photographs of immigrant life from the past century; both through Sept. 6. Hours: Tuesdays, 10 a.m. to 2 p.m. for registered groups only; Wednesdays through Sundays, 10 a.m. to 5 p.m. Suggested admission: $7; 62+, students and children, $4; families, $12. Information: (212) 534-1672.

abstract: LEVINE--Howard R., on July 6th. Devoted father, passionate lawyer, lifelong New Yorker, he is survived by sons Scott of NY and Todd of Fridley, MN, as well as former wife DeLane, also of MN, and brother Robert of Titusville, FL. He was a proud alumnus of Horace Mann '51, University of Pennsylvania '55, and St. John's Law School '58. Memorial service will be held Friday, July 9th, at 2:30 P.M., at Plaza Memorial Chapel, Amsterdam Ave and 91st St. Contributions to Stephen Wise Free Synagogue.

abstract: Profile of and interview with Bea Thomas, 92, popular field hockey coach at Moorestown High School who has been playing and coaching for 70 years; photo (M)
snippet: Profile of and interview with Bea Thomas, 92, popular field hockey coach at Moorestown High School who has been playing and coaching for 70 years; photo (M)
lead_paragraph: TRYING to describe Bea Thomas is a bit like trying to zero in on a moving target. ''Feisty'' is one word that often comes up when people mention her, but that doesn't quite do it. ''Disciplined'' is another, but that's only part of the picture. What most people do when they are trying to sum up Mrs. Thomas, a popular field hockey coach, is to resort to a story.
headline_print_headline: IN PERSON; At 92, Still Teaching Good 'D'

abstract: A selective listing by critics of The Times: New or noteworthy pop and jazz concerts in the New York metropolitan region this weekend. * denotes a highly recommended concert.    * MONTY ALEXANDER, ERNEST RANGLIN, Satalla, 37 West 26th Street, Manhattan, (212) 576-1155. Mr. Alexander, a jazz pianist originally from Jamaica, has often refitted reggae songs and steel-drum sounds for a jazz-trio context. But this weekend he is appearing with Ernest Ranglin, a great Jamaican guitar player now in his 70's, who is one of the backbones of reggae's history. Tonight and tomorrow night at 8 and 10; cover charge is $25 (Ben Ratliff).

abstract: ATTRACTIONS    Museums and Sites    INTREPID SEA-AIR-SPACE MUSEUM, Pier 86, West 46th Street at the Hudson River, Clinton. The Intrepid is a converted World War II aircraft carrier with two decks of displays, including four theme halls: United States Navy Hall, Pioneer Hall, Technologies Hall and Intrepid Hall. ''British Celebration'' includes a tour of the interior of the Concorde, a display of British cars, performances of British rock music, and crafts workshop, tomorrow, 2 to 6 p.m. and Sunday, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. On view: ''All Hands on Deck,'' an interactive exhibition about life aboard a ship; ''Defending Our Future,'' a high-tech, interactive exhibition about the future of military technology; ''Intrepid Remembers 9/11,'' an exhibition of photographs and artwork; ''Prepare to Dive: The 100th Anniversary of the Navy's First Submarine,'' about the pioneering days of the submarine. With screenings of the film ''Concorde Alpha-Delta: An Intrepid Journey,'' that documents the history of the aircraft. Admission: $14.50; 65+, veterans, reservists, students and 65+, $10.50; 6 to 17, $9.50; 2 to 5 years old, $2.50; under 2, active military personnel and museum members, free; wheelchair patrons, half price. Mondays through Fridays, 10 a.m. to 5 p.m.; Saturdays, Sundays and holidays, 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. Information: (212) 245-0072; www.intrepidmuseum.org.
